<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I have a possibility...<P>Telekinisis is the control of objects using just your mind, right?  Well...what about this:<P>A spell that works like so: it must be cast upon a weapon or shield only that is placed upon the ground.  If it is cast upon the weapon, then it (the weapon) shall float and will act like a Pet.  You can then command the weapon to do as pets do, be it attack, defend, etc as if it were a fighter wielding it.  Now, of course, this doesn't include techniques, and perhaps the blade damage can have some lessening ratio to it, to balance it out.  And, of course, it probably will only be able to work on weapons that con yellow to the Sorcerer.  Bows and ranged weapons don't work, as they have to be laoded too.  <P>Now, if you use Telekinisis on a shield, then it cannot attack, but it shall automatically defend you, with a decent-to-high percentage of blocking melee/arrow attacks (higher the spell level, the higher percentage of blocking, right?).  <P>Some points to maybe work out on it: should the controlled weapon/shield have a "life" total so that the weapon/shield can be destroyed?  Of course, it would have to be 100% resistant to mind powers (things that obviously affect things with minds, not inanimate objects like swords).  <P>A good thing about it is that it allows the Sorcerer to have a pet wherever they are: they just have to carry around a sword or shield that they could enchant.  Doing this would make Sorcerers then not want the Charm spell line, as the Telekinisis would obviously be more powerful and useful.  So what could be done to make it balanced?  Could the telekinisis object only last so long before it wears off, and must be cast again?  Should the damage of the weapon be reduced so that a yellow pet will always be more powerful than a yellow weapon?  There are tons of ways to balance this out, and it would put a completely unique twist to the Matter Line.  It would also add a different style of Pets to us, who were once considered to be the "best pet class" (even though currently our only pet choice are ones that are difficult to find, die quickly, cannot be healed, leech more experience than they're worth, etc.).<P>Whatcha think?<P>~Sigma<BR>32 Sorcerer<BR>Percival
</FONT>
