<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Ahem.  I appreciate i3ullseye fighting for the idea, but Battik, I do believe you're quite entitled to yer opinion.<P>If you have suggestions to make the idea better, then certainly, let's hear those.<P>If ye really think that the idea alone is totally worthless, then so be it, I don't share yer opinion but I'll argue to the end for your right to have it and speak it.<P>I might ask though; you say the sword version of the spell is useless.  What about the shield part?  The defensive use of the spell?  Granted, it alone may not be worth fully speccing in Matter.  But I don't think this spell line would be the primary change to Matter; we have to believe there will be other things in it as well.  For each of the other spell categories, you listed at least three things that are in them which are worthwhile; I have to believe that Matter will be the same way, so that a floating sword or shield is not the only thing.<P>As for charming different types of mobs....sure, it'd be useful.  The fact that we can't charm many things (Giants, for instance) is broken pure and simple.  It shouldn't be; the spell says "humanoid", the official class description says "control of the mind", so it'd make sense that any humanoid thing with a mind should be charmable.<P>The Undead, however, do not have a mind.  As it sits now, our Spec DD (Mind blast) does more damage against them than our Life Drain, and I think that's a mistake, since the undead have no minds to flay.  I further don't see us being able to charm undead, since that's completely necromantic (Although, Morgana does it in our epic, though I don't see us being allowed to follow Her path).  And if they did allow us to charm other types of beasts, though a minor thing, the Matter spec name would have to be changed; Telekinesis has little to do with charming.<P>So, some mobs we cannot charm but really *should* be able to with the tools we have now.  <P>Back to the floating item thing...sure, in many senses it'd be like a Cabalist pets.  And I still see them using those, so I'd presume that ours would have its uses as well.  Then there's the issue of the shield half of the spell, which ye haven't addressed.  Finally....granted, this spell alone is not reason enough to fully Spec matter.  But we must remember, it is just an idea for a part of the revamp, not the whole thing itself.
</FONT>
